2057
01:18:13,686 --> 01:18:13,946
It's conserved.

2058
01:18:15,406 --> 01:18:15,706
Certainly,

2059
01:18:15,706 --> 01:18:17,726
the implication goes the other way.

2060
01:18:17,826 --> 01:18:19,406
If a quantity is conserved,

2061
01:18:19,526 --> 01:18:23,486
then its expectation value is time-independent,

2062
01:18:23,486 --> 01:18:23,806
definitely.

2063
01:18:24,286 --> 01:18:25,486
And in that case,

2064
01:18:25,486 --> 01:18:26,946
it must commute with the Hamiltonian.

2065
01:18:27,946 --> 01:18:30,086
The implication goes in both directions.

2066
01:18:30,626 --> 01:18:32,126
If a quantity is conserved,

2067
01:18:32,126 --> 01:18:33,386
it commutes with the Hamiltonian.

2068
01:18:33,426 --> 01:18:35,546
If a quantity commutes with the Hamiltonian,

2069
01:18:35,546 --> 01:18:36,526
then it's conserved.

2070
01:18:36,866 --> 01:18:40,006
But one special case is the Hamiltonian itself.

2071
01:18:40,106 --> 01:18:41,826
Any operator commutes with itself.

2072
01:18:43,686 --> 01:18:45,246
Any operator commutes with itself.

2073
01:18:45,606 --> 01:18:48,106
A times A is equal to A times A,

2074
01:18:48,206 --> 01:18:49,136
and it doesn't matter which

2075
01:18:49,136 --> 01:18:50,066
