2227
01:24:49,166 --> 01:24:50,926
It's related to the momentum.

2228
01:24:51,146 --> 01:24:53,106
It's the square of the momentum divided

2229
01:24:53,106 --> 01:24:55,066
by twice the mass of the particle.

2230
01:24:56,146 --> 01:24:58,996
I've simply used kinetic energy

2231
01:24:58,996 --> 01:25:01,846
as one half m velocity squared,

2232
01:25:02,046 --> 01:25:03,566
and momentum is one half.

2233
01:25:03,586 --> 01:25:04,746
So the energy is m times velocity.

2234
01:25:06,186 --> 01:25:08,606
Just solve this equation for the velocity,

2235
01:25:08,606 --> 01:25:09,846
plug it back into here,

2236
01:25:10,046 --> 01:25:12,466
and the answer is p squared over 2m.

2237
01:25:13,406 --> 01:25:14,546
That suggests,

2238
01:25:14,546 --> 01:25:16,526
does not prove,

2239
01:25:17,506 --> 01:25:19,976
you can never prove something about

2240
01:25:19,976 --> 01:25:22,446
quantum mechanics from the classical physics.

2241
01:25:22,966 --> 01:25:24,826
You can suggest,

2242
01:25:24,826 --> 01:25:26,226
or you can,

2243
01:25:26,226 --> 01:25:26,786
if you like,

2244
01:25:26,786 --> 01:25:27,126
say,

2245
01:25:27,306 --> 01:25:29,736
the classical limit has an energy

2246
01:25:29,736 --> 01:25:32,166
which is p squared over 2m.

2247
01:25:32,166 --> 01:25:34,996
A suggestion and a guess

