01:35:11,876 --> 01:35:14,026
the i p over h bar x in them.

2524
01:35:14,386 --> 01:35:15,826
We can cancel that off.

2525
01:35:15,826 --> 01:35:17,106
Let's cancel that off.

2526
01:35:18,946 --> 01:35:22,926
The rest of it is just an equation for f.

2527
01:35:23,386 --> 01:35:24,946
And it says that f dot,

2528
01:35:24,946 --> 01:35:27,166
the time derivative of f,

2529
01:35:27,166 --> 01:35:28,506
is just,

2530
01:35:28,506 --> 01:35:30,346
let's see,

2531
01:35:30,486 --> 01:35:33,126
there is two powers of i here.

2532
01:35:33,326 --> 01:35:35,526
That's a minus 1 and another i here.

2533
01:35:35,906 --> 01:35:37,346
So that's minus i.

2534
01:35:38,006 --> 01:35:39,246
How many h bars?

2535
01:35:40,106 --> 01:35:40,666
One.

2536
01:35:40,926 --> 01:35:41,906
In the denominator.

2537
01:35:43,185 --> 01:35:48,126
So there's a 2m h bar in the denominator.

2538
01:35:49,186 --> 01:35:50,906
There's a p squared upstairs.

2539
01:35:53,886 --> 01:35:55,026
And an f.

2540
01:35:55,026 --> 01:35:55,846
Is that right?

2541
01:35:56,046 --> 01:35:56,986
I think that's all there is.

2542
01:36:00,546 --> 01:36:00,986
No,

2543
01:36:00,986 --> 01:36:02,786
I cancelled one of the h bars in

2544
01:36:02,786 --> 01:36:04,586
the denominator with the h bar in the top.

2545
01:36:05,626 --> 01:36:07,126
There's two h bars in the denominator.

2546
01:36:09,886 --> 01:36:11,326
Because there was two p's.

2547
01:36:11,326 --> 01:36:13,766
So each p came with an h bar.

2548
01:36:15,026 --> 01:36:15,586
Yeah.

2549
01:36:16,446 --> 01:36:17,446
I think it's right.

2550
01:36:18,986 --> 01:36:19,546
Okay,

2551
01:36:19,546 --> 01:36:21,366
so here we have an equation for f.

2552
01:36:21,586 --> 01:36:23,596
It says that time derivative

2553
01:36:23,596 --> 01:36:25,606
of f is a certain number,

2554
01:36:25,606 --> 01:36:26,806
complex number,

2555
01:36:26,806 --> 01:36:27,806
times f.

2556
01:36:28,586 --> 01:36:29,566
What's the solution?

2557
01:36:30,086 --> 01:36:31,106
An exponential.

2558
01:36:31,586 --> 01:36:32,546
And here it is.

2559
01:36:32,626 --> 01:36:36,756
f is equal to e to

2560
01:36:36,756 --> 01:36:40,886
the minus i p squared over 2m.

2561
01:36:42,126 --> 01:36:44,566
I'll put the h bar next to the i there.

2562
01:36:45,206 --> 01:36:45,986
Times t.

2563
01:36:50,646 --> 01:36:52,046
I've discovered what f is.

2564
01:36:52,166 --> 01:36:59,676
And my whole solution then is e to the i p over

2565
01:36:59,676 --> 01:37:07,186
h bar x minus i p squared over 2m h bar times t.

2566
01:37:08,846 --> 01:37:09,586
That's it.

2567
01:37:09,586 --> 01:37:13,856
That's the solution of the Schrodinger

2568
01:37:13,856 --> 01:37:18,126
equation corresponding to a momentum eigenstate.

2569
01:37:19,226 --> 01:37:21,406
Notice that it changes with time.

2570
01:37:22,486 --> 01:37:24,606
But it changes with time in a very,

2571
01:37:24,606 --> 01:37:25,566
very simple way.

2572
01:37:25,906 --> 01:37:30,006
It changes with time with a pure phase.

2573
01:37:31,186 --> 01:37:33,146
What does that say about the probability?

2574
01:37:33,426 --> 01:37:33,586
Well,

2575
01:37:33,586 --> 01:37:33,906
okay,

2576
01:37:33,906 --> 01:37:36,786
we're now talking about a particular momentum eigenstate.

2577
01:37:37,786 --> 01:37:39,566
We're not talking about a superposition.

2578
01:37:39,566 --> 01:37:40,346
We're not talking about a

2579
01:37:40,346 --> 01:37:41,126
superposition of momentum eigenstates yet.

2580
01:37:41,266 --> 01:37:43,806
This is some specific momentum eigenstate.

2581
01:37:44,026 --> 01:37:45,826
And that's how it varies with time.

2582
01:37:52,086 --> 01:37:54,076
I think we'll quit here and

2583
01:37:54,076 --> 01:37:56,066
come back to this next time.

2584
01:37:56,806 --> 01:37:59,386
We can ask various probability questions.

2585
01:37:59,806 --> 01:38:00,266
We can ask,

2586
01:38:00,266 --> 01:38:00,746
for example,

2587
01:38:00,746 --> 01:38:04,606
